      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.K1Oyu9VpHkaJunnC]{Hypermycology}</p>\n<p>As a standard action, you can create and deliver a potent fungal infection to a creature. When injected, the formula develops in one of three patterns: visual, mental, or physical, chosen as part of your standard action. Targets can attempt a Fortitude saving throw to negate the effects.</p><ul><li><p><strong>@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.effects.Item.bOjsZFLklGr5hRb4]{Visual}:</strong> The targeted creature is silhouetted by a sudden growth of mushrooms. These mushrooms hinder the subjectâ€™s perception, causing a -2 penalty to Perception checks and negating invisibility for 1 minute.</p></li><li><p><strong>Mental:</strong> The targeted creature is @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.Item.8rIj0ewW4bL8Uph5]{Confused} until the end of your next turn.</p></li><li><p><strong>Physical:</strong> The targeted creature is surrounded in a surfeit of gigantic mushrooms that spring up around them, creating an impassible wall in any empty squares adjacent to the creature. The wall has hardness 0 and 5 Hit Points per Biohacker level. The mushrooms wilt and dissipate at the end of your next turn.</p></li></ul>"
